1
00:00:30,920 --> 00:00:39,280
=Echoes of Gang City=

2
00:00:51,640 --> 00:00:57,040
=Episode 17=
(Friends Fight, But They Make Up Easily)

3
00:00:59,060 --> 00:00:59,899
Be careful.

4
00:00:59,900 --> 00:01:01,020
Stay safe.

5
00:01:07,220 --> 00:01:09,659
Boss, Lawyer Fang is moving
the wine cabinet

6
00:01:09,660 --> 00:01:11,260
and the cigar cabinet.

7
00:01:25,500 --> 00:01:28,060
Why don't you tear down
the load-bearing wall while you're at it?

8
00:01:28,220 --> 00:01:29,460
I had someone

9
00:01:29,540 --> 00:01:32,860
custom-built the wine cabinet in Europe.

10
00:01:33,540 --> 00:01:35,140
Someone said

11
00:01:35,260 --> 00:01:37,899
he needs me to drink with him
to fall asleep.

12
00:01:37,900 --> 00:01:39,860
Every bottle I'm taking

13
00:01:40,220 --> 00:01:42,140
is my collection

14
00:01:42,460 --> 00:01:43,860
and my soul.

15
00:01:43,900 --> 00:01:46,220
But all of these were gifts for me.

16
00:01:46,740 --> 00:01:49,299
If I remember correctly,
Article 658 of the Civil Code states...

17
00:01:49,300 --> 00:01:50,700
Mr. Shen.

18
00:02:01,060 --> 00:02:04,180
Are you arguing law with a lawyer?

19
00:02:08,900 --> 00:02:10,020
Wait.

20
00:02:14,460 --> 00:02:17,299
Don't wear that robe to the meeting.

21
00:02:17,300 --> 00:02:19,260
The board will laugh at you
for three months.

22
00:02:24,220 --> 00:02:25,340
Mind your own business.

23
00:02:28,620 --> 00:02:31,659
Our strategic cooperation with Minghui
has been fully terminated.

24
00:02:31,660 --> 00:02:33,339
For the shareholders' meeting,

25
00:02:33,340 --> 00:02:36,180
I've initiated a share buyback plan.

26
00:02:36,300 --> 00:02:39,340
I'm negotiating with the board as well.

27
00:02:48,940 --> 00:02:50,060
Mr. Shen,

28
00:02:51,020 --> 00:02:53,060
I didn't fly here for 12 hours

29
00:02:54,420 --> 00:02:55,820
to hear this.

30
00:02:58,300 --> 00:03:00,140
Have you found out
Shen Gu's background?

31
00:03:02,220 --> 00:03:03,939
His information is protected.

32
00:03:03,940 --> 00:03:05,340
We haven't found anything yet.

33
00:03:05,460 --> 00:03:07,180
After he appeared,

34
00:03:07,660 --> 00:03:09,620
Qingniao invested in Minghui.

35
00:03:10,740 --> 00:03:12,340
Don't you find that weird?

36
00:03:18,660 --> 00:03:19,980
Either

37
00:03:20,540 --> 00:03:23,740
Minghui has close ties with Qingniao,

38
00:03:25,220 --> 00:03:30,380
or Shen Gu can tap into
their core resources.

39
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,480
(Report on Qingniao's Founding Entities)
I need to know

40
00:03:37,480 --> 00:03:39,140
(and Organizational Structure)
who's behind Shen Gu.

41
00:03:40,160 --> 00:03:41,699
(Chairman, President cum CEO)

42
00:03:41,700 --> 00:03:43,580
Since he cares so much about Minghui,

43
00:03:44,820 --> 00:03:48,220
we'll crush Minghui at all costs.

44
00:03:50,820 --> 00:03:54,180
The board won't support that.

45
00:03:56,140 --> 00:03:59,580
Raymond Group will cover
all funding gaps.

46
00:04:00,860 --> 00:04:03,540
Including the eight percent equity
you've pledged.

47
00:04:37,220 --> 00:04:40,780
Gu, how does it feel
to be back in Gang City?

48
00:04:40,820 --> 00:04:42,219
Everyone's going as planned.

49
00:04:42,220 --> 00:04:43,339
Very smooth.

50
00:04:43,340 --> 00:04:47,100
Why isn't Lawyer Fang with you?

51
00:04:48,500 --> 00:04:50,140
He's busy moving house.

52
00:04:50,500 --> 00:04:52,060
Hey, everybody.

53
00:04:52,540 --> 00:04:54,460
I'm late. I apologize.

54
00:04:54,900 --> 00:04:56,220
Traffic was heavy.

55
00:04:56,420 --> 00:04:57,219
I'm so sorry

56
00:04:57,220 --> 00:04:58,179
for being late.

57
00:04:58,180 --> 00:04:59,940
Traffic in Gang City was bad.

58
00:05:00,020 --> 00:05:01,499
Since everyone's here,

59
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:03,819
let's begin.

60
00:05:03,820 --> 00:05:07,140
We have to face reality.

61
00:05:08,900 --> 00:05:11,820
Because you've been appearing
in the media frequently lately.

62
00:05:12,100 --> 00:05:19,339
Rumors that you are
the actual controller behind Qingniao

63
00:05:19,340 --> 00:05:21,180
have spread privately.

64
00:05:21,380 --> 00:05:23,940
Risks such as technology transfer

65
00:05:24,100 --> 00:05:27,180
and data compliance

66
00:05:28,020 --> 00:05:31,619
could crash down on us at any moment.

67
00:05:31,620 --> 00:05:35,019
Gu, your identity
and Qingniao's investment portfolio

68
00:05:35,020 --> 00:05:38,540
will be subject to
endless over-interpretation.

69
00:05:38,820 --> 00:05:40,980
The global supply chain
is interconnected.

70
00:05:41,420 --> 00:05:42,699
Any shift in sentiment

71
00:05:42,700 --> 00:05:44,099
affects our local partners'

72
00:05:44,100 --> 00:05:46,060
confidence.

73
00:05:47,860 --> 00:05:48,980
Are you done?

74
00:05:50,100 --> 00:05:51,180
Everyone,

75
00:05:51,820 --> 00:05:53,939
I've been aware of these risks

76
00:05:53,940 --> 00:05:56,940
earlier and more clearly than you.

77
00:05:57,620 --> 00:06:00,460
That's why I've kept my identity hidden.

78
00:06:00,620 --> 00:06:04,820
No matter what comes next,
technical barriers or monopolies,

79
00:06:05,020 --> 00:06:07,580
we'll fight fairly, by the rules.

80
00:06:08,540 --> 00:06:10,980
We have the best legal team,

81
00:06:11,060 --> 00:06:13,740
and we're prepared to spend
whatever it takes

82
00:06:13,820 --> 00:06:15,339
to prove

83
00:06:15,340 --> 00:06:19,620
what fair competition
and contract integrity mean.

84
00:06:20,740 --> 00:06:22,380
My identity

85
00:06:22,500 --> 00:06:24,260
stays undisclosed for now.

86
00:06:24,620 --> 00:06:28,780
It's to minimize damage.

87
00:06:31,020 --> 00:06:33,260
What I'm trying to say is

88
00:06:34,900 --> 00:06:36,340
that this is not just a challenge,

89
00:06:36,860 --> 00:06:39,140
it's also an irreplaceable advantage.

90
00:06:40,260 --> 00:06:41,979
Proceed with everything

91
00:06:41,980 --> 00:06:44,180
according to plan.

92
00:06:45,500 --> 00:06:46,740
Good luck to all of us.

93
00:06:47,340 --> 00:06:49,859
Since signing Su Mei as our ambassador,

94
00:06:49,860 --> 00:06:53,019
the public sentiment index on our side
is up 127 percent.

95
00:06:53,020 --> 00:06:54,680
Weekly product sales

96
00:06:54,680 --> 00:06:56,619
(Reports on Sales)
have increased by 34.6 percent.

97
00:06:56,620 --> 00:06:57,780
(and Public Sentiment Statistic)
Excellent news.

98
00:06:59,010 --> 00:07:00,219
Anjie,

99
00:07:00,220 --> 00:07:02,939
how's the termination with Junlin going?

100
00:07:02,940 --> 00:07:04,140
It's smooth overall.

101
00:07:04,220 --> 00:07:06,540
But the cooperation
is deeply intertwined.

102
00:07:07,500 --> 00:07:08,780
It'll take time.

103
00:07:09,700 --> 00:07:10,619
Our priority

104
00:07:10,620 --> 00:07:13,459
is to fully cut ties with Junlin Group

105
00:07:13,460 --> 00:07:15,220
to avoid future risks.

106
00:07:15,620 --> 00:07:16,740
Okay.

107
00:07:17,020 --> 00:07:19,339
The legal department will complete
all termination procedures

108
00:07:19,340 --> 00:07:20,940
within 30 working days.

109
00:07:21,260 --> 00:07:22,380
Very well.

110
00:07:23,020 --> 00:07:24,140
Wanxin.

111
00:07:26,300 --> 00:07:28,060
What's wrong, Mr. Changhe?

112
00:07:28,540 --> 00:07:30,699
Our five core raw material suppliers

113
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:32,560
have all sent termination notices
at the same time.

114
00:07:32,900 --> 00:07:33,900
Have a look.

115
00:07:34,660 --> 00:07:36,220
All five at the same time?

116
00:07:36,900 --> 00:07:37,979
If the supply chain breaks,

117
00:07:37,980 --> 00:07:40,060
we'll suffer major losses.

118
00:07:40,620 --> 00:07:42,899
Someone is targeting us.

119
00:07:42,900 --> 00:07:44,299
Who else but Junlin Group

120
00:07:44,300 --> 00:07:46,180
could do this?

121
00:07:53,420 --> 00:07:54,540
Don't worry.

122
00:07:55,520 --> 00:07:57,260
There's always a solution.

123
00:08:00,520 --> 00:08:03,320
(Grandfather)

124
00:08:13,820 --> 00:08:14,859
Grandfather.

125
00:08:14,860 --> 00:08:16,059
Shen Gu,

126
00:08:16,060 --> 00:08:18,019
Junlin Group

127
00:08:18,020 --> 00:08:21,060
took away our core material suppliers.

128
00:08:21,260 --> 00:08:23,899
It'll take time

129
00:08:23,900 --> 00:08:25,820
to fully resolve this.

130
00:08:26,540 --> 00:08:29,459
Since Wanxin took over the company,

131
00:08:29,460 --> 00:08:31,979
there hasn't been a day
without trouble.

132
00:08:31,980 --> 00:08:33,619
She's been stuck in her office

133
00:08:33,620 --> 00:08:36,220
working all day.

134
00:08:36,420 --> 00:08:37,820
I understand, Grandfather.

135
00:08:38,380 --> 00:08:40,219
When Zhaoming was around,

136
00:08:40,220 --> 00:08:43,500
he could always talk her through
moments like this.

137
00:08:44,340 --> 00:08:46,140
Given what has happened now,

138
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:48,860
it's best if you handle this.

139
00:08:49,420 --> 00:08:50,659
Don't worry, Grandfather.

140
00:08:50,660 --> 00:08:52,419
I'll pick her up from Minghui later

141
00:08:52,420 --> 00:08:54,419
and bring her back to see you.

142
00:08:54,420 --> 00:08:55,769
Good.

143
00:08:55,770 --> 00:08:57,699
I was just saying yesterday

144
00:08:57,700 --> 00:09:00,580
I wanted to have dinner with you.

145
00:09:01,940 --> 00:09:03,380
See you later.

146
00:09:03,740 --> 00:09:04,860
Alright.

147
00:09:17,820 --> 00:09:19,740
Is everything packed?

148
00:09:21,100 --> 00:09:22,220
Are you

149
00:09:22,660 --> 00:09:23,780
kicking me out?

150
00:09:24,020 --> 00:09:25,740
It's one street away.

151
00:09:25,860 --> 00:09:27,140
I won't see you off.

152
00:09:32,420 --> 00:09:33,540
What are you doing?

153
00:09:33,620 --> 00:09:36,940
I bought this from Sotheby's.

154
00:09:38,540 --> 00:09:40,419
I'm having dinner
with Grandfather tonight.

155
00:09:40,420 --> 00:09:42,940
I thought I'd let him try
the Islay flavor.

156
00:09:48,020 --> 00:09:50,380
Leave the cigar cabinet here.

157
00:09:50,540 --> 00:09:52,420
A reason for you to come back anytime.

158
00:09:56,420 --> 00:09:57,580
Okay.

159
00:09:58,940 --> 00:10:00,060
Right.

160
00:10:00,780 --> 00:10:03,780
Next time you come back,
give me a heads-up first.

161
00:10:05,340 --> 00:10:09,140
He might prefer Chinese bajiu.

162
00:10:35,520 --> 00:10:36,640
Wanxin,

163
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:39,319
how about we shortlist
some suppliers first?

164
00:10:39,320 --> 00:10:40,720
You haven't eaten anything all day.

165
00:10:41,720 --> 00:10:43,840
I'm not hungry. We're short on time.

166
00:10:44,120 --> 00:10:45,880
We need to make a decision quickly.

167
00:10:56,560 --> 00:10:57,920
What are you doing here?

168
00:11:00,238 --> 00:11:03,518
I'm here to invite Ms. Wanxin to dinner.

169
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:06,760
I'm busy. I have no appetite.

170
00:11:35,040 --> 00:11:36,880
Still worrying about suppliers?

171
00:11:39,400 --> 00:11:41,840
I've talked to the suppliers
we used to work with.

172
00:11:41,920 --> 00:11:43,919
They terminated the contracts

173
00:11:43,920 --> 00:11:45,280
under pressure from Junlin.

174
00:11:45,720 --> 00:11:48,040
Even if I find new suppliers,

175
00:11:48,400 --> 00:11:49,920
this might happen again.

176
00:11:53,240 --> 00:11:55,320
I'm stressed out, and you're laughing.

177
00:12:03,920 --> 00:12:06,359
They're pressured by Junlin

178
00:12:06,360 --> 00:12:07,640
not to work with you,

179
00:12:07,720 --> 00:12:11,480
but that doesn't mean
they can't work with other companies.

180
00:12:11,920 --> 00:12:13,240
That makes sense.

181
00:12:13,520 --> 00:12:15,439
Instead of looking for new suppliers,

182
00:12:15,440 --> 00:12:17,519
I should look at
their partner companies.

183
00:12:17,520 --> 00:12:19,319
Find ones that have ties with Minghui

184
00:12:19,320 --> 00:12:20,840
and set up third-party contracts.

185
00:12:21,120 --> 00:12:22,760
I'll call Diana right away.

186
00:12:24,400 --> 00:12:26,040
Let's have dinner first.

187
00:12:26,520 --> 00:12:28,440
Where are we going?

188
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:32,120
You're laughing again.

189
00:12:40,840 --> 00:12:41,719
This...

190
00:12:41,720 --> 00:12:43,360
This is the road back
to Grandfather's place.

191
00:12:45,520 --> 00:12:47,240
He missed you.

192
00:13:12,600 --> 00:13:13,840
Grandfather.

193
00:13:17,160 --> 00:13:20,040
Why did you come out, Grandfather?

194
00:13:20,920 --> 00:13:23,719
I heard you didn't eat all day.

195
00:13:23,720 --> 00:13:27,319
I had them prepare
a few dishes you like.

196
00:13:27,320 --> 00:13:29,360
Fish maw and mutsutake mushroom
chicken soup.

197
00:13:29,440 --> 00:13:31,319
It's made in the traditional way.

198
00:13:31,320 --> 00:13:32,999
You'll definitely like it.

199
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:34,520
You love me the most, Grandfather.

200
00:13:34,880 --> 00:13:36,400
Come on, let's eat.

201
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:49,720
That's more like it.

202
00:13:49,920 --> 00:13:53,120
You need to eat well
to have energy for work.

203
00:13:54,080 --> 00:13:55,679
Grandfather,

204
00:13:55,680 --> 00:13:58,119
you already know
what happened to the company?

205
00:13:58,120 --> 00:13:59,240
Mm.

206
00:13:59,840 --> 00:14:01,920
I just took over not long ago.

207
00:14:02,280 --> 00:14:05,320
I wanted to prove myself quickly,

208
00:14:05,640 --> 00:14:06,920
so I got a bit anxious.

209
00:14:08,680 --> 00:14:11,360
When your dad first took over,

210
00:14:11,400 --> 00:14:15,240
he'd secretly go to hotels
and cry by himself.

211
00:14:15,320 --> 00:14:17,509
He'd call me at 3 AM

212
00:14:17,510 --> 00:14:18,839
and say, "Dad,

213
00:14:18,840 --> 00:14:21,079
our research project failed.

214
00:14:21,080 --> 00:14:22,400
What do we do?"

215
00:14:23,760 --> 00:14:24,719
I can say

216
00:14:24,720 --> 00:14:25,819
that's true.

217
00:14:25,820 --> 00:14:26,679
Your father

218
00:14:26,680 --> 00:14:28,519
started out just like that too.

219
00:14:28,520 --> 00:14:30,720
So I take after him.

220
00:14:31,240 --> 00:14:33,320
Don't learn that from him.

221
00:14:33,600 --> 00:14:35,119
Running a company

222
00:14:35,120 --> 00:14:37,719
means you'll make wrong decisions
sometimes.

223
00:14:37,720 --> 00:14:39,919
They can be fixed.

224
00:14:39,920 --> 00:14:44,360
What matters is holding on
to the company spirit.

225
00:14:44,840 --> 00:14:45,839
To benefit the people

226
00:14:45,840 --> 00:14:47,119
and to strengthen the nation.

227
00:14:47,120 --> 00:14:49,840
I'll remember that as Dad did.

228
00:14:50,320 --> 00:14:51,440
Good.

229
00:14:51,720 --> 00:14:53,960
Aren't you going to have a drink
with me?

230
00:14:54,040 --> 00:14:56,039
You're just looking for an excuse
to drink again.

231
00:14:56,040 --> 00:14:57,999
The liquor tastes good,

232
00:14:58,000 --> 00:14:59,239
but you shouldn't drink too much.

233
00:14:59,240 --> 00:15:00,600
One last glass.

234
00:15:02,720 --> 00:15:04,359
Shen Gu brought this.

235
00:15:04,360 --> 00:15:05,839
Why shouldn't I drink it?

236
00:15:05,840 --> 00:15:07,480
Then just one last glass.

237
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:09,080
Alright.

238
00:15:09,480 --> 00:15:11,400
Grandfather, a toast to you.

239
00:15:22,200 --> 00:15:23,320
Nice.

240
00:15:24,480 --> 00:15:25,599
If you like it,

241
00:15:25,600 --> 00:15:26,799
I'll bring you more next time.

242
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:28,320
Sure.

243
00:15:30,400 --> 00:15:33,360
You've had some liquor tonight.
Don't go back.

244
00:15:33,640 --> 00:15:35,639
Stay here

245
00:15:35,640 --> 00:15:37,800
and keep me company.

246
00:15:39,680 --> 00:15:40,439
Alright.

247
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:41,520
I'll do as you say.

248
00:15:41,560 --> 00:15:43,119
I haven't arranged

249
00:15:43,120 --> 00:15:45,640
a proper home for you two yet.

250
00:15:46,400 --> 00:15:50,360
Tonight, you'll stay in Wanxin's room.

251
00:15:50,800 --> 00:15:52,320
Grandfather.

252
00:15:52,880 --> 00:15:54,120
Changhe,

253
00:15:54,680 --> 00:15:56,760
I think I'm a bit tipsy.

254
00:15:58,600 --> 00:15:59,920
I'm tired.

255
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:01,719
Help me get back to rest.

256
00:16:01,720 --> 00:16:02,760
Alright.

257
00:16:03,720 --> 00:16:05,240
Take it slow.

258
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:07,800
Okay.

259
00:16:07,920 --> 00:16:09,800
Get some rest early, Grandfather.

260
00:16:11,280 --> 00:16:13,640
Enjoy the food.

261
00:16:55,640 --> 00:17:01,440
♪Tonight the rain falls soft and slow♪

262
00:17:02,720 --> 00:17:08,520
♪Blending with letters left unread
drifting through the air♪

263
00:17:09,240 --> 00:17:14,600
♪You turn and look back at me♪

264
00:17:15,720 --> 00:17:21,240
♪In those same eyes familiar tears
quietly appear♪

265
00:17:22,080 --> 00:17:27,720
♪It feels like we have carried so much♪

266
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:34,480
♪So many questions time itself
could not make clear♪

267
00:17:35,600 --> 00:17:40,920
♪The moment you walked into my life♪

268
00:17:42,080 --> 00:17:47,880
♪Every dream I had became something
I want with you near♪

269
00:17:48,280 --> 00:17:55,240
♪How many letters have I written
just for you?♪

270
00:17:55,360 --> 00:18:01,040
♪If only you could truly hear
what my heart is trying to say♪

271
00:18:01,720 --> 00:18:08,079
♪From this life on
no distance could keep us apart♪

272
00:18:08,080 --> 00:18:10,959
♪The promise we made♪

273
00:18:10,960 --> 00:18:14,639
♪Will find its way to be fulfilled
one day♪

274
00:18:14,640 --> 00:18:21,239
♪But I want more
than just that fleeting gaze♪

275
00:18:21,240 --> 00:18:27,640
♪Still I have not heard your answer♪

276
00:18:28,040 --> 00:18:34,359
♪Can we still rewrite the ending
we face?♪

277
00:18:34,360 --> 00:18:39,480
♪When regrets begin to turn around you
